latestIgtvVideos.title: Double Cleansing
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hey guys, have you ever heard of double cleansing? If not, then I am here to the rescue. LOL 
Well, as the name suggests double cleansing is cleansing twice but with 2 different cleansers. First you use any micellar water, oil or balm to cleanser your face, it breaks down all the makeup, sebum, or any product that you applied during the day and clean out clogged pores like blackheads or whiteheads. The 2nd time you use any water based cleanser to do the deep cleaning that targets bacteria, dead skin or acne. 
For this particular procedure I am using oil. You can take any cleansing oil but I use coconut oil. For dry skin you can use coconut oil, olive oil, avocado oil and sweet almond oil. If your skin is acne prone then don't use coconut oil. There are other options for it like jojoba and argan oil. But do your research before using any product on your skin and do a patch test first. There are many skincare brands that have introduced cleansing oils, you can try that also. For acne prone skin try to find an oil cleanser that is noncomedogenic.

Procedure:
Massage your face with oil for 2 to 3 minutes. Then take a wet, clean towel and microwave it for 30 seconds, you can do it for 20 seconds as well. If it feels so hot for your skin to endure wait a few seconds then put it on your face. Wait for 5 minutes and keep pressing it on the face so the heat is absorbed properly. Clean your face mildly with the same towel, so all the excess oil is removed. Now take your regular but gentle cleanser, I am using @biodermame here and cleanse for another 2 to 3 minutes. Be very gentle with your skin then wash your face. After that take an ice cube and rub it on your face specially cheeks and forhead for minimising the pores. You can also use any toner that's available. 
This routine feels like a mini spa at home and my skin feels really soft, glowy and clean after it. I specifically do it when I see some blackheads or whiteheads popping on the surface of the skin. It really helps me clean them.

Let me know if it was helpful and feel free to ask any questions. ❤

p.s: Please see my comment for additional steps that I did in the video.

latestPosts.caption:
From Korangi to Dubai, My Journey So Far

I come from a town called Korangi in Karachi. Life was not easy, we came from a humble background. My father worked tirelessly; his day job didn’t pay enough so he drove a taxi after hours just to make ends meet. His dedication shaped my understanding of hard work and sacrifice from a young age.

I studied at a government college and earned my bachelor’s degree. Like many others, I was searching for a job, unsure of what was next. But life had a surprise waiting for me and I was awarded an MBA scholarship through a Pakistani TV show called Inam Ghar on Geo Tv Network (Story for another day). That moment changed everything.

I pursued my MBA while working during the weekdays and classes during the weekends. I still remember switching two buses every single day just to get to work and university. It was not glamorous, but it taught me the value of persistence and patience. Every late night and long commute were a step toward something greater.

Later on, I moved to Dubai, with no idea where the journey would take me. Starting over in a new country was overwhelming, but it gave me the space to grow and the opportunities that I could not even think of in my wildest dreams. Today, I am far from where I started, but not yet where I want to be.

Little Maira with big dreams would be so proud of me. My life journey is still ongoing, but one thing is clear, I know my goal, and I will keep moving forward until I get there.

#Lifejourney #Daretodream #Dreambig #fromkorangitodubai
